---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
        <head>
                <BaseHead
                        title={`About ${SITE_TITLE}`}
                        description="Who we are, what problems we solve, and how to collaborate with us."
                />
                <style>
                        .about-grid {
                                display: grid;
                                grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 1fr;
                                gap: 1.5rem;
                        }
                        .callout {
                                padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
                                background: rgba(var(--accent), 8%);
                                border: 1px solid rgba(var(--accent), 12%);
                                border-radius: 12px;
                        }
                        .timeline {
                                list-style: none;
                                padding: 0;
                                margin: 0;
                                display: grid;
                                gap: 1rem;
                        }
                        .timeline li {
                                border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
                                padding-left: 1rem;
                        }
                        @media (max-width: 900px) {
                                .about-grid {
                                        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
                                }
                        }
                </style>
        </head>
        <body>
                <Header />
                <main>
                        <p class="pill">About ntrcaexplore.com</p>
                        <h1>Built for educators navigating the NTRCA process.</h1>
                        <p>
                                NTRCA Explore was created to simplify the recruitment journey. We publish short explainers,
                                checklists, and reminders so candidates spend less time deciphering notices and more time preparing
                                their documents and interviews.
                        </p>

                        <div class="about-grid">
                                <section class="panel">
                                        <h2>What you can expect</h2>
                                        <p class="muted">
                                                Each article is written to be clear, repeatable, and easy to act on—perfect for teachers who are
                                                busy with classrooms and coaching.
                                        </p>
                                        <ul class="timeline">
                                                <li>
                                                        <strong>Practical breakdowns.</strong> Step-by-step instructions for online applications, document uploads,
                                                        payments, and corrections.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>
                                                        <strong>Alerts, not noise.</strong> Only the key dates, eligibility changes, and subject wise updates make it into
                                                        the feed.
                                                </li>
                                                <li>
                                                        <strong>Reusable templates.</strong> Copy-friendly checklists and drafts that you can adapt to your own workflow.
                                                </li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <div class="callout">
                                                Have an idea or correction? Send a note to <a href="mailto:hello@ntrcaexplore.com">hello@ntrcaexplore.com</a>
                                                and we’ll fold it into the next update.
                                        </div>
                                </section>
                                <aside class="panel">
                                        <h3>How to contribute</h3>
                                        <p class="muted">
                                                Use the Content Panel to draft posts, export Markdown, and drop the files in <code>src/content/blog</code>.
                                                If you want to collaborate through GitHub, open an issue describing the resource you’d like to see.
                                        </p>
                                        <h3>Editorial guardrails</h3>
                                        <ul class="checklist">
                                                <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> Keep steps short and actionable.</li>
                                                <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> Cite official circulars or notices when summarizing changes.</li>
                                                <li><span class="checkmark">✓</span> Offer links to supporting documents whenever possible.</li>
                                        </ul>
                                        <div class="callout">
                                                If you’re reading this offline, visit <strong>ntrcaexplore.com</strong> for the latest version.
                                        </div>
                                </aside>
                        </div>
                </main>
                <Footer />
        </body>
</html>
